channel.title: Free developer if anyone wants me
channel.description:
Sick of applying for roles really... honestly its a bit pathetic when you add questions like "Why do you want to work for me". Well its not really a question you get to ask when youre looking for someone to work free...
Im wanting to join a team relativly fast, would prefer if the build was below 508 but im not really bothered. Add me on skype if you're intrested: exotiicdeath

item.description:

[quote=“Bellend, post:7, topic:549423”][quote author=Ruby link=topic=668325.msg4469812#msg4469812 date=1422343022]
I run by a very strict guideline of by name, by nature.

I have a mate named Simon Dick, he’s a dick by name and a dick by nature. This makes you a bellend by name and a bellend by nature.

Good day.
[/quote]

Double standards. Ruby’s are shiney, expensive and precious. You dont come close to any of them. GG GF.[/quote]

Hahahahhaha, well played. +1 for having some kind of sense of humour.

item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Bellend:

Mmmm not really, if you apply that logic in real terms then charaties would be much harder to work for. I see where you’re coming from but we have to set a middle ground somewhere.

In this case, you should be posting your pro’s…
I.E: Past projects, history in rsps, history in programming, etc.

If I were looking for a partner, I wouldn’t consider you because I know nothing about you.
Good luck though.

item.title: Free developer if anyone wants me
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Same goes for you and looking for a team…

Why should I add you to my team? I’m a perfectly fine developer on my own. What makes me want to add you to my team? You’ve posted no background information about you, nor any previous works. And it’s not like your name is known around here like some of the past “greats”.

And you have to keep in mind that here on moparscape, we’re not really allowed to talk about finances for a server. It’s in the rules we cannot offer rewards, or the like. So, I mean, technically, people cannot say “paying a developer”. You’d have to ask them via pm or off site.
